<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
As mentioned above, Berlese's 1910 record of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Brachychthoniidae" genus="Brachychthonius" genus.bestMatchDistance="48" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">B. brevis</taxonomicName>
refers to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Brachychthoniidae" genus="Brachychthonius" genus.bestMatchDistance="58" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berlesei">B. berlesei</taxonomicName>
Willmann. This species is known from several countries in Europe; there are many preparations of it in the Berlese Collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
I remark that Berlese (1896b, p. 25), in an introduction to the classification of Oribatid mites, also mentioned 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hypochthoniidae" genus="Hypochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">Hypochthonius brevis</taxonomicName>
(among the representatives of the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hypochthoniidae" genus="Hypochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hypochthoniidae</taxonomicName>
); because reference is made to Michael's specimens only, this record certainly relates to the real 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Brachychthoniidae" genus="Brachychthonius" genus.bestMatchDistance="131" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">B. brevis Michael</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
